$ SQL Server function: object_definition
@ object_definition

Use the → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions/object_id[`object_id(…)`] function to find the id of a particular object, then use this id with `object_definition` to display
the object's definition.

gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/functions/object_definition/select.sql||

sa:

  The definition of an object is also stored in the → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/sql_modules[`sql_modules`] view.

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions
